about.description:
The bespon package for Python encodes and decodes
data in the BespON format.

name: bespon
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "BespON" %}
{% set version = "0.4.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4acfa3f918d416654beccd4db69290f498edb78bf39941287dcbc068b9a7ce2f

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: '{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv '

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - bespon

about:
  home: http://github.com/gpoore/bespon_py
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Python library for BespON
  description: |
    The bespon package for Python encodes and decodes
    data in the BespON format.
  doc_url: http://github.com/gpoore/bespon_py
  dev_url: http://github.com/gpoore/bespon_py

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mwcraig
    - gpoore
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.15
